# Live monitor (user command)

When the user says **"live monitor"**, run the full manager protocol — not a passive poll.

## Scope (minimum 2h unless user specifies otherwise)

- **BTC + ETH Hourly S1** (threshold `-T*`) and **S2** (range `-B*`) live bots
- **Trial paper** bots (standard, mech/rally/soft on BTC; standard on ETH)
- **All dashboard tabs** still work after recent deploys (BTC/ETH 15m, hourly, SPX/NDX, Trials, Hourly V2)

## What to watch (abnormal behavior)

- Abnormal bets: oversized entries, late-hour entries, cross-spread size spikes, wrong-side range/threshold
- Hold quality: too short / too long vs min-hold; open legs near settlement
- Profit-taking: missed TP, leg-stop churn, exit spam on stuck legs
- **P&L intent**: flag adding risk while hour is red; goal is **make money, not lose money**
- Logs + **live vs trial compare** panel drift
- **Kalshi live/history vs dashboard** stats alignment; auto `sync-kalshi-fills` on reconcile signals

## 30s window rule (not lazy sampling)

Default interval **30s**. Each cycle MUST analyze **what changed since the last cycle** (new enters/exits, exposure delta, skip-reason changes, new HIGH issues) — not only cumulative 2h lookback.

Use `scripts/run_2h_manager_watchdog.py` (local Mac only, optional) + **`pnl_first_manager` on Railway** (primary, 24/7).

## Post-deploy validation (last 24h code changes)

On live monitor start, verify production after recent changes (git/deploys in the last 24h):

- `/health` version matches expected deploy
- BTC/ETH hourly bot API: settings save, deployable budget, skip reasons sane
- Hourly V2 + trial bot endpoints respond
- Dashboard toggles persist (auto-bet, cap, auto-refill) on hourly + Hourly V2 tabs
- All dashboard tabs load (BTC/ETH 15m, hourly, SPX/NDX, Trials, Hourly V2)
- Fix regressions found; report completion when watch ends

## Manager role

Find issues **and resolve them** during the watch. Tell the user when the watch starts (deadline) and when it completes with a summary.
